# Autonomous Development System Rules

## Task Execution

- Before editing code, check `memory/architecture.md` for module ownership and dependencies.
- Update task status in both the task file (`tasks/task_XXX.md`) and the database after completion.
- Run tests before marking a task as `done`.
- Never mark a task done if dependencies are not fully completed.

## Task Format

Tasks use this format in markdown files:

```
id: T001
title: implement parser
status: todo
priority: 1
dependencies: []
owner: composer_1
```

Valid statuses: `todo`, `in_progress`, `done`, `blocked`.

## Code Ownership

- Respect the code ownership map in `memory/architecture.md`.
- When modifying a module owned by another agent, document the change and reason.
- Avoid modifying modules outside your assigned scope unless necessary.

## Architecture

- Do not introduce circular dependencies.
- Follow layer hierarchy defined in `memory/architecture.md`.
- When adding new modules, update `memory/architecture.md` or create a task for Researcher to do so.

## Triggers

- Every 20 tasks: Researcher runs (context compression).
- Every 50 tasks: Meta Planner runs (DAG optimization).
- Every 200 tasks: Auditor runs (architecture audit).

## Commands

Use `dreamteam` CLI, not python scripts:
- dreamteam run-next, dreamteam update-task, dreamteam task-counter
- dreamteam verify-tasks, dreamteam sync-tasks, dreamteam recover

## Console & UI

- Write console logs and UI messages in English.
